@startuml
' @id(SEQ-KICKOFF)
' @ref(USE-KICKOFF)
' @desc(SEQ-KICKOFF, "The /mdd-kickoff flow: preflight greenfield; interview the developer to objective+architecture alignment (clarify, never guess); write .mdd/docs/brief.md and STOP at a sign-off gate; on approval run /mdd-generate for the full objective then /mdd-validate; decompose the objective into a foundations-first priority-ordered PLAN.md where model-bearing items carry inline @scope(<id>,…) and infra items carry none; STOP with a summary and the next command. Never launches Ralph.")
' Objective sequence for the greenfield kickoff front door (cycle 0027,
' greenfield-kickoff Cycle B).
title Greenfield kickoff flow (objective)

actor "Developer" as Dev
participant "/mdd-kickoff" as K
participant "/mdd-generate" as Gen
participant "/mdd-validate" as Val
participant ".mdd/docs/brief.md" as Brief
participant ".mdd/ralph/PLAN.md" as Plan

Dev -> K : /mdd-kickoff [idea]
K -> K : preflight — repo is greenfield?
loop until the developer confirms alignment
  K -> Dev : clarifying question (objective / architecture / tooling)
  Dev --> K : answer
end
K -> Brief : write objective, scope, ADR-lite decisions, tooling, NFRs
K -> Dev : present brief for sign-off
note right of Dev: SIGN-OFF GATE — no model before alignment
Dev --> K : approve
K -> Gen : generate the FULL objective from the agreed brief
Gen --> K : objective model
K -> Val : validate
Val --> K : clean
K -> Plan : decompose foundations-first; model items carry @scope, infra items none
K -> Dev : summary + next command (review brief + PLAN, then /mdd-ralph)
note right of K: STOP — never launches Ralph
@enduml
